On the 26/12 at the time of my last prediction I had retained only elements that could reduce the number of cases in the weeks to come:
- the massive festive gatherings are over (Christmas, New Year, vacations);
- people will be outdoors more because the days are longer (the virus is less transmitted outdoors);
- Vaccination (vaccination begins in the USA);
- Biden is president instead of Trump, so people are better informed rationally. Two factors could potentially increase the number of recorded cases:
- A policy of more massive use of screening tests due to the arrival of Biden. However, to the best of my knowledge, there is currently no indication that this will be put in place;
- a new epidemic wave: unlikely due to the above;
-the arrival of the more contagious variant (but vaccine is effective against). I still think that these elements are coherent.
As for the speed of the decrease in slope, I think that extrapolations from the current slopes of @Closed-loop are consistent and even show rather a pessimistic scenario, which does not take into account the factors mentioned above.
